The paper discusses user privacy concerns in smart cyber-physical systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the implementation of privacy protection in a smart home scenario, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper identifies challenges in achieving effective privacy management for smart cyber-physical systems, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
